subSubSection.paragraph:
Description.
Male (
Holotype
, Senador Porfirio, Pará, 
Brazil
, MPEG 4994). Total length 7.18. Carapace 3.59 long, 3.32 wide, light brown. Clypeus yellow with two median bristles, 0.52 high. Anterior eye row straight, 0.92 wide (
Fig. 25
); posterior recurved, 1.38 wide. Eye diameters, interdistances, and median ocular quadrangle: AME 0.21, ALE 0.09, PME 0.20, PLE 0.26; AME-AME 0.16, AME-ALE 0.12, PME-PME 0.26, PME-PLE 0.28, OQA 0.44, OQP 0.70, OQH 0.60. Chelicerae reddish-brown, laterally depressed and with a large tuft of small white bristles (
Fig. 25
). Sternum yellow, with scattered bristles; 1.55 long, 1.64 wide. Labium light brown, yellowish distally, 0.34 long, 0.55 wide. Legs light brown, unmarked; relative length: I-IV-II-III, I—femur 5.56/ patella-tibia 7.63/ metatarsus 5.39/ tarsus 2.57/ total 21.15; II—5.31/ 6.80/ 4.73/ 2.24/ 19.08; III—3.40/ 4.56/ 3.32/ 1.32/ 12.60; IV—5.89/ 6.97/ 5.38/ 2.65/ 20.89. Ventral pairs of macrosetae on tibiae: I-5; II-5; III-3; IV-4. Superior tarsal claw with 11 teeth and inferior with one tooth (
Fig. 102
). Abdomen 3.60 long, light brown with two parallel dark brown bands on distal half; with two pairs of sigillae. Venter gray, with scattered bristles. Palpus with an elongated median apophysis with an acute tip (
Figs 98, 99, 100
). Ental branch of RTA with a lamellar projection at the base and a slender and thin apex (
Fig. 100
); ectal branch of RTA divided in two branches (
Fig. 100
).

Female (
Paratype
, Almeirim, Pará, 
Brazil
, MPEG 6786). Total length 6.80. Carapace 3.15 long, 2.82 wide, colour as in male. Clypeus yellow, 0.34 high. Anterior eye row straight, 0.80 wide; posterior recurved, 1.36 wide. Eye diameters, interdistances, and median ocular quadrangle: AME 0.16, ALE 0.09, PME 0.20, PLE 0.24; AME- AME 0.16, AME-ALE 0.08, PME-PME 0.26, PME-PLE 0.28, OQA 0.48, OQP 0.66, OQH 0.52. Chelicerae light brown, with scattered bristles. Sternum yellow, 1.41 long, 1.40 wide. Labium as in male, 0.49 long, 0.48 wide. Legs light brown, unmarked; relative length: I-II-IV-III, I—femur 5.14/ patella-tibia 6.80/ metatarsus 4.56/ tarsus 1.66/ total 18.16; II—4.64/ 6.30/ 4.31/ 1.82/ 17.07; III—3.32/ 3.90/ 2.73/ 1.32/ 11.27; IV—4.31/ 5.64/ 4.06/ 1.82/ 15.83. Ventral pairs of macrosetae on tibiae: I-4; II-4; III-3; IV-4. Abdomen 3.81 long, colouration as in male. Epigynum with a projected median portion of the middle field (
Figs 103, 104
) and with conspicuous circular hoods. Sclerotized pocket (
Fig. 105
), prominent circular copulatory ducts (CD1 and CD 2) (
Fig. 105
) and with a slender head of spermathecae with pores (
Fig. 106
).
